597 17.816C4.81947 18.5686 5.43139 19.1805 6.18404 19.564C7.03968 20 8.15979 20 10.4 20H14C15.8638 20 16.7956 20 17.5307 19.6955C18.5108 19.2895 19.2895 18.5108 19.6955 17.5307C20 16.7956 20 15.8638 20 14V14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="square"></path><path d="M12.4393 14.5607L19.5 7.5C20.3284 6.67157 20.3284 5.32843 19.5 4.5C18.6716 3.67157 17.3284 3.67157 16.5 4.5L9.43934 11.5607C9.15804 11.842 9 12.2235 9 12.6213V15H11.3787C11.7765 15 12.158 14.842 12.4393 14.5607Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="square"></path></svg></a></span></div></div></div><div class="relative flex h-full flex-col items-center @container/chat min-w-[340px] [--content-max-width:32rem] @[44rem]:[--content-max-width:40rem] @[52rem]:[--content-max-width:48rem] [--content-gutter:1rem] [--thead-sticky-top:0rem] @xl/mainview:[--thead-sticky-top:0px] breakout"><div class="absolute right-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 z-20"></div><div class="w-full h-full overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden scrollbar-gutter-stable flex flex-col items-center px-gutter" style="overflow-anchor: none;"><div class="relative flex w-full flex-col items-center pt-20 pb-4"><div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-19aa068a-625c-45b0-9e26-7e40a67a6369" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Excellent choice ŌĆö exporting the graph turns this from ŌĆ£it runsŌĆØ into ŌĆ£it reveals structureŌĆØ.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Below are drop-in additions to your mock kernel that let you export the current relational state as:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Graphviz DOT (great for sanity checks, papers, static views)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Streaming-friendly JSON (perfect for your 3D semantic space explorer)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">IŌĆÖll give you:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">additions to sp_mock_kernel.h</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">implementation in sp_mock_kernel_export.c</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">usage examples (including live replay streaming)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Everything is conservative C, no clever tricks.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Header additions</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Add to sp_mock_kernel.h</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* Export / visualization
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* Export entire graph in Graphviz DOT format.
&nbsp;* If collapse_reps != 0, nodes are grouped by union-find representative.
&nbsp;<span>*/
sp_status_t sp_mk_export_dot(const sp_mk_t*</span> mk,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;FILE* out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int collapse_reps);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* Export entire graph as JSON.
&nbsp;* Format is stable and streaming-friendly.
&nbsp;* If collapse_reps != 0, ids are mapped to representatives.
&nbsp;<span>*/
sp_status_t sp_mk_export_json(const sp_mk_t*</span> mk,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;FILE* out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int collapse_reps);</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Implementation</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">New file: sp_mock_kernel_export.c</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* sp_mock_kernel_export.c */
#include "sp_mock_kernel.h"
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* Helpers
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static sp_handle_t rep_id(const sp_mk_t* mk, sp_handle_t id, int collapse) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (!collapse) return id;
&nbsp;&nbsp;/* const cast ok: find does path compression but is idempotent <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;return sp_mk_find((sp_mk_t*</span>)mk, id);
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* DOT export
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ <span>*/
sp_status_t sp_mk_export_dot(const sp_mk_t*</span> mk,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;FILE* out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int collapse_reps) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (!mk || !out) return SP_EINVAL;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "digraph spherepop {\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "  rankdir=LR;\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "  node [shape=ellipse, style=filled, fillcolor=lightgray];\n");</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Nodes <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;for (uint32_t i = 0; i &lt; mk-&gt;objs_len; i++) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_obj_t*</span> o = &amp;mk-&gt;objs[i];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t id = rep_id(mk, o-&gt;id, collapse_reps);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const char* shape = "ellipse";
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (o-&gt;objtype == SP_OT_REGION) shape = "box";
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (o-&gt;objtype == SP_OT_ORDER)  shape = "diamond";</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"  "%llu" [label="%llu\n(type=%u)", shape=%s];\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)id,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)id,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)o-&gt;objtype,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;shape);
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Edges <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;for (uint32_t i = 0; i &lt; mk-&gt;edges_len; i++) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_edge_t*</span> e = &amp;mk-&gt;edges[i];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t src = rep_id(mk, e-&gt;src, collapse_reps);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t dst = rep_id(mk, e-&gt;dst, collapse_reps);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const char* style = (e-&gt;link_flags &amp; SP_LF_SOFT) ? "dashed" : "solid";
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const char* color = (e-&gt;link_flags &amp; SP_LF_CAUSAL) ? "red" : "black";</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"  "%llu" -&gt; "%llu" [label="r=%u", style=%s, color=%s];\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)src,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)e-&gt;reltype,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;style,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;color);
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "}\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;return SP_OK;
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* JSON export
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ <span>*/
sp_status_t sp_mk_export_json(const sp_mk_t*</span> mk,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;FILE* out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;int collapse_reps) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (!mk || !out) return SP_EINVAL;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "{\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "  "objects": [\n");</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;for (uint32_t i = 0; i &lt; mk-&gt;objs_len; i++) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_obj_t* o = &amp;mk-&gt;objs[i];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t id = rep_id(mk, o-&gt;id, collapse_reps);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"    {"id": %llu, "type": %u, "rep": %llu}",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)o-&gt;id,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)o-&gt;objtype,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)id);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (i + 1 &lt; mk-&gt;objs_len) fprintf(out, ",");
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "  ],\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "  "edges": [\n");</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;for (uint32_t i = 0; i &lt; mk-&gt;edges_len; i++) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_edge_t* e = &amp;mk-&gt;edges[i];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t src = rep_id(mk, e-&gt;src, collapse_reps);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t dst = rep_id(mk, e-&gt;dst, collapse_reps);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"    {"src": %llu, "dst": %llu, "rel": %u, "
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;""flags": %u}",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)src,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)e-&gt;reltype,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e-&gt;link_flags);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (i + 1 &lt; mk-&gt;edges_len) fprintf(out, ",");
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "  ]\n");
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(out, "}\n");</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;return SP_OK;
}</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Using it (static export)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Export after replay</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Add this to the end of sp_replay_mock_main.c:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">FILE* f_dot = fopen("graph.dot", "w");
sp_mk_export_dot(&amp;mk, f_dot, 1);
fclose(f_dot);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">FILE* f_json = fopen("graph.json", "w");
sp_mk_export_json(&amp;mk, f_json, 1);
fclose(f_json);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Then:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">dot -Tsvg graph.dot &gt; graph.svg</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="4">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Live export during replay (for your 3D explorer)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Replace apply_any with:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static sp_status_t apply_any(sp_replay_ctx_t* ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_event_hdr_t* hdr,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const void* payload) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_t* mk = (sp_mk_t*)ctx-&gt;user;
&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Stream incremental JSON */
&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_export_json(mk, stdout, 1);
&nbsp;&nbsp;fflush(stdout);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;return SP_OK;
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Now your renderer can read a continuous stream of full semantic states.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Why this matters architecturally</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You now have:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A deterministic semantic world</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A causal history</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A visualizable manifold</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A clean separation between:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">kernel semantics (Spherepop calculus),</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">replay logic (time / causality),</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">presentation (3D explorer, VR, whatever)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is exactly how an OS should feel when built from first principles.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Natural next steps (pick one)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you want, next I can add:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Incremental diffs (emit only changed nodes/edges per event)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Layout hints (attach suggested 3D positions as meta blobs)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Entropy visualization (map S to color/opacity/instability)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Interactive controls (merge/split from the UI ŌåÆ event injection)</li>
