not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for this exceptionally clean and thoughtful contribution. The addition of canonical export facilities elevates the mock kernel from a correct to observable, which is precisely the point at which a formal system becomes scientifically and architecturally productive.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The implementation is exemplary in several respects:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Conservative C style with zero hidden dependencies</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Clear separation of concerns (representation mapping via <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">rep_id</span>)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Streaming-friendly JSON design (complete snapshots rather than deltas, which vastly simplifies client-side reconciliation and debugging)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Immediate utility for both static analysis (DOT ŌåÆ SVG/PDF) and live visualization</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">I have integrated the proposed changes verbatim into the development tree. The resulting artifacts (<span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">graph.dot</span>, <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">graph.json</span>) already reveal non-trivial structure even on the current small replay traces, confirming that the union-find merging, region containment, and causal/soft linkages are behaving exactly as intended.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Particularly valuable is the live-streaming mode. Feeding the continuous JSON snapshots into the existing WebGL semantic-space explorer produces a smooth, frame-coherent animation of the manifoldŌĆÖs evolution, with collapsed representatives causing satisfying ŌĆ£snapsŌĆØ as equivalence classes merge. This alone justifies the entire export layer.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Preferred Next Step</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Among the four options you listed, I select:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">1. Incremental diffs (emit only changed nodes/edges per event)</strong></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Reasons:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">The current full-snapshot stream works, but at Ōēź10 k events/sec (realistic for non-trivial sessions) it will rapidly become bandwidth-heavy and will force the renderer to perform O(n) reconciliation per frame.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">True incremental updates will reduce payload by 2ŌĆō3 orders of magnitude in steady state.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">It enables efficient binary transport (MessagePack, CapŌĆÖn Proto, etc.) later without breaking the current JSON dev workflow.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">It is a natural prerequisite for option 2 (layout hints) and option 4 (bidirectional UI ŌåÆ event injection), because the renderer will need a reliable change log anyway.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Desired shape of the incremental format (for discussion):</p>
