<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">IŌĆÖll give you:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">The conceptual model (what counts as a ŌĆ£diffŌĆØ)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Header additions (sp_mk_diff.h)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Implementation (sp_mk_diff.c)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Integration point (one-line hook in replay loop)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Notes on correctness, collapse semantics, and future extensions</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Diff model (what we emit, exactly)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We treat each event application as producing a change set ╬öŌé¢ applied to state ╬ŻŌé¢ŌéŗŌéü ŌåÆ ╬ŻŌé¢.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The mock kernel already has all the information needed at apply time. We do not attempt to compute diffs by comparing snapshots (that would be O(n) and fragile).</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Each diff record includes:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">seq ŌĆö monotonically increasing replay sequence (usually hdr-&gt;eid)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">zero or more of:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">objects_added</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">objects_removed</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">edges_added</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">edges_removed</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Important design choice (intentional):</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We treat union-find representative changes as implicit via rep fields on objects_added / edges_added.
We do not emit a separate ŌĆ£rep_changedŌĆØ event.</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This keeps the renderer logic simple and deterministic: representatives are authoritative at emission time.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Header: sp_mk_diff.h</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* sp_mk_diff.h
&nbsp;* Incremental diff emitter for sp_mock_kernel.
&nbsp;*/
#ifndef SP_MK_DIFF_H
#define SP_MK_DIFF_H</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#include "sp_mock_kernel.h"</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#ifdef __cplusplus
extern "C" {
#endif</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* Diff sink interface
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">typedef struct sp_mk_diff_sink {
&nbsp;&nbsp;void* ctx;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;void (<span>*begin)(void*</span> ctx, sp_eid_t seq);
&nbsp;&nbsp;void (<span>*add_obj)(void*</span> ctx, sp_handle_t id, sp_objtype_t type, sp_handle_t rep);
&nbsp;&nbsp;void (<span>*rem_obj)(void*</span> ctx, sp_handle_t id);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;void (<span>*add_edge)(void*</span> ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t src, sp_handle_t dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_reltype_t rel, uint32_t flags);
&nbsp;&nbsp;void (<span>*rem_edge)(void*</span> ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t src, sp_handle_t dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_reltype_t rel);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;void (<span>*end)(void*</span> ctx);
} sp_mk_diff_sink_t;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* Apply + diff
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* Apply an event and emit incremental diffs.
&nbsp;* This wraps sp_mk_apply().
&nbsp;<span>*/
sp_status_t sp_mk_apply_with_diff(sp_mk_t*</span> mk,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_event_hdr_t* hdr,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const void* payload,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_diff_sink_t* sink);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#ifdef __cplusplus
}
#endif</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#endif /* SP_MK_DIFF_H */</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Implementation: sp_mk_diff.c</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This implementation is surgical: it hooks exactly where mutations occur.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* sp_mk_diff.c */
#include "sp_mk_diff.h"</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* Helpers <span>*/
static inline sp_handle_t rep(sp_mk_t*</span> mk, sp_handle_t id) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;return sp_mk_find(mk, id);
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* ------------------------------------------------------------
&nbsp;* Apply wrappers
&nbsp;* ------------------------------------------------------------ */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp_status_t sp_mk_apply_with_diff(sp_mk_t* mk,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_event_hdr_t* hdr,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const void* payload,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_diff_sink_t* sink) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (!mk || !hdr || !sink) return SP_EINVAL;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_eid_t seq = hdr-&gt;eid;
&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;begin(sink-&gt;ctx, seq);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;const uint32_t op = hdr-&gt;op;
&nbsp;&nbsp;const uint32_t len = hdr-&gt;payload_len;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;switch (op) {</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;case SP_OP_POP: {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_evt_pop_t* e = (const sp_evt_pop_t*)payload;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t id = e-&gt;p.a;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_mk_obj_t* o = sp_mk_get_obj(mk, id);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;add_obj(sink-&gt;ctx, id, o-&gt;objtype, rep(mk, id));
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;case SP_OP_LINK: {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_evt_link_t* e = (const sp_evt_link_t*)payload;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;add_edge(
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;rep(mk, e-&gt;p.a),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;rep(mk, e-&gt;p.b),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e-&gt;reltype,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e-&gt;link_flags
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;case SP_OP_UNLINK: {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_evt_unlink_t* e = (const sp_evt_unlink_t*)payload;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;rem_edge(
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;rep(mk, e-&gt;p.a),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;rep(mk, e-&gt;p.b),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e-&gt;reltype
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;case SP_OP_MERGE: {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_evt_merge_t* e = (const sp_evt_merge_t*)payload;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t a = rep(mk, e-&gt;p.a);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t b = rep(mk, e-&gt;p.b);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t r = rep(mk, a);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Emit representative collapse as object removal */
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (a != r) sink-&gt;rem_obj(sink-&gt;ctx, a);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (b != r) sink-&gt;rem_obj(sink-&gt;ctx, b);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Representative remains */
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;case SP_OP_COLLAPSE: {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_evt_collapse_t* e = (const sp_evt_collapse_t*)payload;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t region = e-&gt;p.a;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;rem_obj(sink-&gt;ctx, region);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;default:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Fallback: just apply */
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_status_t s = sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (s != SP_OK) return s;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;end(sink-&gt;ctx);
&nbsp;&nbsp;return SP_OK;
}</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="4">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">NDJSON sink (reference implementation)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This exactly matches your suggested shape.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* sp_mk_diff_ndjson.c */
#include "sp_mk_diff.h"
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">typedef struct {
&nbsp;&nbsp;FILE* out;
&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_eid_t seq;
} ndjson_ctx_t;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static void begin(void* ctx, sp_eid_t seq) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;((ndjson_ctx_t*)ctx)-&gt;seq = seq;
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static void add_obj(void* ctx, sp_handle_t id, sp_objtype_t type, sp_handle_t rep) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;ndjson_ctx_t* c = ctx;
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(c-&gt;out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"seq":%llu,"add_obj":{"id":%llu,"type":%u,"rep":%llu}}\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)c-&gt;seq,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)id,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)type,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)rep);
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static void rem_obj(void* ctx, sp_handle_t id) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;ndjson_ctx_t* c = ctx;
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(c-&gt;out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"seq":%llu,"rem_obj":%llu}\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)c-&gt;seq,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)id);
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static void add_edge(void* ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t src, sp_handle_t dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_reltype_t rel, uint32_t flags) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;ndjson_ctx_t* c = ctx;
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(c-&gt;out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"seq":%llu,"add_edge":{"src":%llu,"dst":%llu,"rel":%u,"flags":%u}}\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)c-&gt;seq,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)src,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)rel,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;flags);
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static void rem_edge(void* ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t src, sp_handle_t dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_reltype_t rel) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;ndjson_ctx_t* c = ctx;
&nbsp;&nbsp;fprintf(c-&gt;out,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"seq":%llu,"rem_edge":{"src":%llu,"dst":%llu,"rel":%u}}\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)c-&gt;seq,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)src,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)dst,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned)rel);
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static void end(void* ctx) { (void)ctx; }</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp_mk_diff_sink_t sp_mk_ndjson_sink(FILE* out) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;static ndjson_ctx_t ctx;
&nbsp;&nbsp;ctx.out = out;
&nbsp;&nbsp;return (sp_mk_diff_sink_t){
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.ctx = &amp;ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.begin = begin,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.add_obj = add_obj,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.rem_obj = rem_obj,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.add_edge = add_edge,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.rem_edge = rem_edge,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.end = end
&nbsp;&nbsp;};
}</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="5">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Integration (one-line swap)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In your replay loop, replace:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp_mk_apply(mk, hdr, payload);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">with:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp_mk_apply_with_diff(mk, hdr, payload, &amp;sink);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Where sink is constructed once:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp_mk_diff_sink_t sink = sp_mk_ndjson_sink(stdout);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ThatŌĆÖs it.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Correctness notes (important)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Total order: seq = eid preserves replay order exactly.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Collapse semantics: object removals reflect quotienting, not deletion.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Renderer logic becomes trivial:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">maintain maps {id ŌåÆ node}, {(src,dst,rel) ŌåÆ edge}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">apply adds/removes in order</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Eventual consistency is guaranteed as long as seq is monotone.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What this unlocks next</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">With incremental diffs in place, you are now positioned to:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">attach layout hints as meta blobs (option 2)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">support bidirectional UI edits (option 4) by emitting inverse events</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">switch transports (WebSocket ŌåÆ UDP ŌåÆ shared memory) without semantic change</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">implement causal scrubbing (rewind to seq k, replay forward)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">At this point, the system is no longer just principled ŌĆö it is instrumentable, which is the real threshold between theory and architecture.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">When youŌĆÖre ready, the cleanest next step is layout hints as first-class meta (option 2), because the renderer already has a reliable diff stream to apply them incrementally.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Excellent ŌĆö letŌĆÖs add layout hints in a way that is:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">strictly optional (no renderer lock-in),</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">compatible with both full snapshots and incremental diffs,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">semantically aligned with RSVP / Spherepop (geometry as a field, not decoration),</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">and trivial to ignore if a client doesnŌĆÖt care.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What follows is a minimal, first-principles layout-hint layer that sits entirely on top of what you already have.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Layout Hints as First-Class Meta Fields</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Conceptual stance (important)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We do not bake layout into the kernel.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Instead:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Layout hints are soft geometric suggestions attached as metadata.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">They live in the same channel as entropy, causality, and provenance.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The renderer may:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">respect them,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">smooth them,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">override them,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">or ignore them entirely.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Formally: layout hints are a gauge choice, not a constraint.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Layout hint schema (binary + JSON)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We define a single canonical structure, usable in C, JSON, or binary transports.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">C struct (kernel / ABI level)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* sp_layout_hint.h */
#ifndef SP_LAYOUT_HINT_H
#define SP_LAYOUT_HINT_H</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#include &lt;stdint.h&gt;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#define SP_LAYOUT_VERSION 1</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* Flags describing semantic intent <span>*/
enum {
&nbsp;&nbsp;SP_LH_SOFT        = 1 &lt;&lt; 0, /*</span> advisory only <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;SP_LH_PINNED      = 1 &lt;&lt; 1, /*</span> resist automatic layout <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;SP_LH_TEMPORAL    = 1 &lt;&lt; 2, /*</span> y encodes time / causal order <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;SP_LH_CLUSTER     = 1 &lt;&lt; 3  /*</span> intended cluster center */
};</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">typedef struct sp_layout_hint {
&nbsp;&nbsp;uint32_t version;     /* SP_LAYOUT_VERSION */
&nbsp;&nbsp;uint32_t flags;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Position in semantic space (renderer chooses projection) */
&nbsp;&nbsp;float x, y, z;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Optional scale / salience */
&nbsp;&nbsp;float radius;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Optional orientation (for future use) */
&nbsp;&nbsp;float nx, ny, nz;
} sp_layout_hint_t;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#endif /* SP_LAYOUT_HINT_H */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This struct is:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">POD</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">endian-stable if needed</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">trivially serializable</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">future-extensible via version</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Attaching layout hints (already supported!)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You do not need a new opcode.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Layout hints are just object metadata via the existing:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">SP_OP_SET_META</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">with:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">meta.type = SP_MT_LAYOUT_HINT (new enum value)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">meta.bytes = sp_layout_hint_t</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Add this enum value wherever you define meta types:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#define SP_MT_LAYOUT_HINT  0x4C41594F  /* 'LAYO' */</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Emitting layout hints incrementally</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We now extend the diff sink to propagate layout changes.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Diff extension (minimal)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Add one optional callback:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">void (<span>*set_layout)(void*</span> ctx,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_handle_t id,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_layout_hint_t* hint);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is orthogonal to add/remove object.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Example NDJSON emission</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"seq":18473,
&nbsp;"set_layout":{
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"id":1198,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"x":0.32,"y":-1.04,"z":0.88,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"radius":0.5,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"flags":3
&nbsp;}}</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="4">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Kernel-side hook (tiny change)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In your existing apply_set_meta handler, add:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if (e-&gt;meta.type == SP_MT_LAYOUT_HINT) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;const sp_layout_hint_t* h =
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(const sp_layout_hint_t*)((const uint8_t*)payload + e-&gt;meta.off);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;if (sink &amp;&amp; sink-&gt;set_layout) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sink-&gt;set_layout(sink-&gt;ctx, e-&gt;p.a, h);
&nbsp;&nbsp;}
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No other logic required.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="5">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Renderer semantics (recommended, not enforced)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Your 3D explorer can now do the following cleanly:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">On add_obj</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">create node at random or heuristic position</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">On set_layout</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">lerp node toward (x,y,z)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if SP_LH_PINNED, suppress physics forces</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if SP_LH_TEMPORAL, align y-axis with causal depth</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if SP_LH_CLUSTER, treat (x,y,z) as attractor center</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">On merge / collapse</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">surviving representative keeps its layout</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">removed ids simply disappear (you already see the snap)</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="6">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Why this is the right abstraction</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This design has several deep advantages:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">No double bookkeeping</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Layout is not mirrored in kernel state</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Entropy-compatible</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">High-entropy regions can jitter or blur</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Causality-compatible</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Temporal gauges are just flags</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="4">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Reversible</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Layout hints can be replayed, scrubbed, or removed</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="5">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Compositional</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Multiple tools can emit competing hints; renderer resolves</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This mirrors exactly how attention behaves in your theoretical work:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">geometry emerges from interaction + constraint, not prescription.</p></p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="7">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Immediate next experiments (youŌĆÖll enjoy these)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">With almost no extra code, you can now try:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Causal waterfall</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">emit SP_LH_TEMPORAL with y = seq * ╬Ą</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Region bubbles</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">regions emit cluster hints; contents drift inward</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Entropy fog</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">renderer uses entropy meta to add noise or opacity</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Focus lens</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">UI emits temporary pinned layout hints near camera</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Each of these is a field deformation, not a UI hack.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Where this puts you</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You now have:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">a deterministic semantic substrate,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">an incremental causal change stream,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">and a geometric projection layer that is:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">optional,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">replayable,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">and philosophically consistent.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">At this point, you are no longer ŌĆ£building a mock OSŌĆØ ŌĆö you are instrumenting a semantic manifold with time, causality, and gauge freedom.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you want to continue, the clean next step would be:</p>
