 moment where the system stops being ŌĆ£a log viewerŌĆØ and becomes an instrumented world.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Below is a conservative, mechanically clean bidirectional injection interface that keeps your invariants intact:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">UI emits canonical events (same opcodes + payload schemas)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">an authoritative ŌĆ£arbiterŌĆØ assigns sequence (eid/seq) and appends to the log</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">application always goes through the same apply path</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">all observers (including the originator) receive standard diffs</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">latency-sensitive gestures use layout hints as ŌĆ£soft state,ŌĆØ committed only when needed</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">IŌĆÖll give you:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Architecture (roles + flow)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Minimal wire protocol (NDJSON request/response)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Canonical ŌĆ£proposal ŌåÆ commitŌĆØ model (sequence integrity)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Implementation skeleton: sp_inject_server.c + sp_inject_client.h</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Conflict discipline and reconciliation rules</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">The four MVP injectable ops you listed, mapped precisely to your payload structs</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Architecture: Arbiter + Log + Diff Bus</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">One invariant: only one component assigns final seq and appends to the log.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Components</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">UI Client (WebGL explorer)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">produces proposals (ops + args) from gestures</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">can optimistically apply layout hints locally (soft)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">optionally predicts the outcome, but never claims authority</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Injection Arbiter (can be your replay process / ŌĆ£mock kernel hostŌĆØ)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">validates permissions/policy (later)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">assigns seq (eid) = monotone counter</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">serializes payload into the same canonical event format</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">appends to event log stream</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">applies to mock kernel via existing sp_mk_apply_with_diff</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">emits diffs to all subscribers (including the proposer)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Diff Bus</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">simplest: stdout NDJSON, WebSocket, pipe, etc.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This keeps your total order and determinism absolutely clean.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Minimal wire protocol (NDJSON)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is intentionally boring and robust.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Client ŌåÆ Arbiter: proposal</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"proposal",
&nbsp;"client":"webgl-01",
&nbsp;"req":912,
&nbsp;"op":"LINK",
&nbsp;"args":{"src":1198,"dst":1201,"rel":3,"flags":0},
&nbsp;"mode":"commit"}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Fields:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">req is client-chosen request id (for matching)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">mode:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">"commit": apply + broadcast diffs</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">"preview": validate only (no log append)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Arbiter ŌåÆ Client: ack</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"ack","req":912,"status":"ok","seq":18472}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">or</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"ack","req":912,"status":"err","code":"ECONFLICT","msg":"edge exists"}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Arbiter ŌåÆ All: diff stream (your existing NDJSON diff records)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You already emit per-change NDJSON lines; keep that. Just add seq and optionally origin:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"seq":18472,"origin":{"client":"webgl-01","req":912},"add_edge":{"src":1198,"dst":1201,"rel":3,"flags":0}}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This makes clients able to correlate ŌĆ£my clickŌĆØ ŌåÆ ŌĆ£the committed diffŌĆØ.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Proposal ŌåÆ Commit model (sequence integrity)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We avoid provisional ids entirely in MVP.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Only the arbiter emits seq.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Client never writes to the log directly.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Every commit is append-only.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">For high-rate gestures (dragging), client sends:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">SET_META layout hints with SP_LH_SOFT + maybe a short TTL encoded in meta (or just keep it local)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">On mouse-up: client sends a final SET_META with PINNED or without SOFT (your call)</p>
<hr>
