<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">4b) sp_inject_server.c (arbiter that receives proposals, commits events, emits diffs)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This version assumes:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">proposals arrive as NDJSON lines on stdin</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">diffs go to stdout</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">it appends events to an events.bin file in canonical header+payload format</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ItŌĆÖs intentionally minimal. (Parsing NDJSON robustly is a bigger topic; for MVP we can accept ŌĆ£well-formed linesŌĆØ or use a tiny JSON parser later.)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">/* sp_inject_server.c
&nbsp;*
&nbsp;* Minimal injection arbiter:
&nbsp;*  - reads proposal lines (stdin)
&nbsp;*  - converts to canonical event (hdr + payload)
