roup-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="More actions" id="radix-_r_5ij_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-ellipsis size-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="1"></circle></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-1cbf1125-d618-49c3-922b-a7bc78f9bc33" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Absolutely ŌĆö WebSocket is the right ŌĆ£production-likeŌĆØ transport here, and you can keep it dependency-light by implementing a minimal RFC6455 server (no TLS, text frames only, single-threaded poll() loop). That preserves your architectural discipline: one authoritative arbiter, append-only log, canonical apply-with-diff, broadcast diffs, origin-correlated acks.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Below is a native WebSocketŌĆōadapted arbiter that:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">listens on TCP (default :8765)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">accepts multiple concurrent clients</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">performs WebSocket handshake (SHA1 + base64, implemented inline)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">treats each incoming text frame as one NDJSON proposal line (exactly your model)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">emits:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ack to the originating client</p>
