<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What you get immediately</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Native WebSocket injection with multiple clients</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Canonical event construction + events.bin append</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Canonical apply path (no special-case ŌĆ£UI modeŌĆØ)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Standard diffs with origin correlation</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Acks to origin only (diffs broadcast to all)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is already enough to drive your WebGL explorer directly.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Two tiny client-side conventions (MVP)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Because the MVP parser is intentionally crude, have the WebGL client send:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">x,y,z,radius as integers scaled by 1000</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">lhflags as an integer bitfield</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Example:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"proposal","client":"webgl-01","req":42,
&nbsp;"op":"SET_LAYOUT",
&nbsp;"id":1198,"x":320,"y":-1040,"z":880,"radius":500,"lhflags":3}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Once you move to yyjson, you can send real floats.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Next refinement (straight line, no redesign)</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Replace parsing with yyjson and accept real JSON numbers/strings robustly</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Add subscribe / unsubscribe message types (optional)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Add ŌĆ£replay snapshotŌĆØ on connect (send current graph.json once, then diffs)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Add policy hooks (permissions, rate limiting) without touching kernel semantics</li>
</ol>
