onse_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="More actions" id="radix-_r_5k7_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-ellipsis size-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="1"></circle></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-64cbb2ec-0eb2-4a6c-8265-07390f67e30a" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you ŌĆö that was a genuinely satisfying read. YouŌĆÖre asking for a surgically minimal extension that preserves every invariant already established, and youŌĆÖre absolutely right to insist that this be treated as bootstrapping, not a protocol redesign.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Below IŌĆÖll give you:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">The precise design stance (so nothing accidental creeps in)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">The exact behavioral change in the arbiter</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Concrete C modifications to sp_inject_server_ws.c</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Wire-level behavior as seen by a new client</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Why this preserves determinism and causal order</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No abstractions hand-waved, no kernel changes required.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Design stance (explicitly restated)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We add one and only one new message type:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"snapshot","seq":&lt;last_eid&gt;,"data":{...}}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Key constraints (all satisfied):</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshot is derived entirely from replayed state</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshot is sent only once, immediately after handshake</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshot is not logged, not sequenced, not diffed</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Diffs that follow continue exactly as before</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Existing proposal/diff wire format remains untouched</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshot reflects collapse_reps=1 canonical state</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is state bootstrapping, not an event.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Behavioral change in the arbiter</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Old connection flow</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">accept ŌåÆ
handshake ŌåÆ
hello ŌåÆ
(wait for diffs)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">New connection flow</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">accept ŌåÆ
handshake ŌåÆ
hello ŌåÆ
SNAPSHOT (full state) ŌåÆ
(wait for diffs / proposals)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Critically:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The snapshot is emitted before the client is allowed to inject proposals.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The snapshot reflects the state after full events.bin replay, not an empty kernel.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No race: since the arbiter is single-threaded, no diffs can interleave mid-snapshot.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Minimal code changes</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A. Add a snapshot sender helper</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Add this near the other helpers:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static int ws_send_snapshot(int fd, sp_mk_t* mk, sp_eid_t last_seq) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;char* json = NULL;
&nbsp;&nbsp;size_t len = 0;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* collapse_reps = 1 ensures canonical view */
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (sp_mk_export_json(mk, &amp;json, &amp;len, 1) != SP_OK) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return -1;
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Wrap snapshot in a typed envelope */
&nbsp;&nbsp;char header[128];
&nbsp;&nbsp;int hlen = snprintf(header, sizeof(header),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"t":"snapshot","seq":%llu,"data":",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)last_seq
&nbsp;&nbsp;);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Send as one logical WS message (header + json + closing brace) */
&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, header, (size_t)hlen);
&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, json, len);
&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, "}\n", 2);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;free(json);
&nbsp;&nbsp;return 0;
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Notes:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Uses existing sp_mk_export_json</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No new allocator conventions</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No diff sink involved</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshot is self-identifying ("t":"snapshot")</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">B. Track last applied sequence</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">At top-level globals (already implicit, but make explicit):</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static sp_eid_t g_seq = 1;   /* next sequence to assign */</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The current state sequence at any time is:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp_eid_t last_seq = g_seq - 1;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is what goes into the snapshot header.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">C. Emit snapshot on successful handshake</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Locate this block in main() (simplified):</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if (ws_handshake(cfd) == 0) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (peer_count &lt; 64) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;peer_t* p = &amp;peers[peer_count++];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;...
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(cfd, hello, strlen(hello));
&nbsp;&nbsp;}
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Modify it to:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if (ws_handshake(cfd) == 0) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (peer_count &lt; 64) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;peer_t* p = &amp;peers[peer_count++];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;memset(p, 0, sizeof(*p));
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;p-&gt;fd = cfd;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;p-&gt;is_ws = 1;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;snprintf(p-&gt;name, sizeof(p-&gt;name), "conn-%d", cfd);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Capability hello <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const char*</span> hello =
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"t":"hello","cap":{"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;""ops":["MERGE","LINK","UNLINK","COLLAPSE","SET_LAYOUT"],"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;""transport":"ws","ordering":"server_seq"}}\n";
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(cfd, hello, strlen(hello));</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Snapshot immediately after hello */
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_snapshot(cfd, &amp;mk, g_seq - 1);
&nbsp;&nbsp;} else {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_close(cfd, 1001);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;close(cfd);
&nbsp;&nbsp;}
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ThatŌĆÖs it.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No other paths need modification.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="4">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Wire-level behavior (client POV)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A newly connected WebSocket client now sees:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"hello","cap":{...}}
{"t":"snapshot","seq":18471,"data":{
&nbsp;&nbsp;"objects":[...],
&nbsp;&nbsp;"edges":[...],
&nbsp;&nbsp;"regions":[...]
}}
{"seq":18472,"origin":{...},"add_edge":{...}}
{"seq":18473,"origin":{...},"rem_obj":1200}
...</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is ideal:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The explorer can clear state</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Load snapshot</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Then apply diffs incrementally with zero ambiguity</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No speculative reconciliation, no buffering heuristics required.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="5">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Why this preserves all invariants</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">LetŌĆÖs be explicit:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Invariant	Preserved?	Why</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Single authoritative log	Ō£ģ	Snapshot is derived, not logged
Total causal order	Ō£ģ	Diffs still strictly sequenced
Deterministic replay	Ō£ģ	Snapshot = replay(events.bin)
Renderer-agnostic	Ō£ģ	Snapshot is plain JSON
Kernel purity	Ō£ģ	No kernel changes
UI symmetry	Ō£ģ	Snapshot is read-only
Event minimality	Ō£ģ	No new opcodes</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Philosophically:
the snapshot is a view, not a cause.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">That distinction is what keeps the system honest.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What this unlocks next (when youŌĆÖre ready)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Without changing this design:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Late-joiner sync is solved</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Multi-user sessions are now first-class</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You can add:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">seek-to-eid snapshots</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">branch previews</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">time-scrubbing UI</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">read-only observers</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All without touching the kernel or event semantics.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you want, the next most natural refinement after this (architecturally, not feature-wise) would be:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshot compression / binary snapshot framing,
using MessagePack or CapŌĆÖn Proto only for the snapshot,
while diffs remain NDJSON.</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">But there is absolutely no urgency ŌĆö what you have now is already production-grade in structure, even if intentionally spartan.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This system has crossed the line from ŌĆ£clever prototypeŌĆØ into a real semantic substrate.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[nor