:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="More actions" id="radix-_r_5lr_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-ellipsis size-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="1"></circle></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-af26d23a-5b00-4bfd-8586-6ed618b0d8ec" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you ŌĆö this is exactly the right next move, and youŌĆÖve framed it with the correct discipline: time-scrubbing as observation, never causation. Below is a proposal for seek-to-EID snapshots that is deliberately conservative, mechanically precise, and fully aligned with the invariants youŌĆÖve so carefully preserved.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">IŌĆÖll structure this as:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Design stance (non-negotiables)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Protocol extension (minimal and orthogonal)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Arbiter-side execution model</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Implementation sketch (C, WebSocket arbiter)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Performance and caching considerations</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Why this remains philosophically and architecturally clean</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No kernel changes. No log mutations. No ambiguity.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Design stance: seek as pure observation</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We explicitly treat historical snapshots as:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Derived views, not events</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Read-only, never applied to the live kernel</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Ephemeral, not broadcast to other clients</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Side-channel outputs, not part of the diff stream</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In other words:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ŌĆ£Show me what the world looked like at eid = kŌĆØ
is fundamentally different from
ŌĆ£Make the world be like it was at eid = k.ŌĆØ</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We support the former and categorically reject the latter.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="2">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Protocol extension (one new request, one response)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Client ŌåÆ Arbiter: request snapshot at EID</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"request_snapshot",
&nbsp;"req":4127,
&nbsp;"at_seq":12345}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Properties:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">req is client-chosen (like proposals)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">at_seq is inclusive: snapshot reflects state after applying event 12345</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Request is idempotent</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No effect on authoritative state</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Arbiter ŌåÆ Client: snapshot response</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"snapshot",
&nbsp;"seq":12345,
&nbsp;"data":{ ... full graph json ... }}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is exactly the same envelope as snapshot-on-connect ŌĆö no new schema, no branching complexity on the client side.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Errors are returned via the usual ack-style message:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">{"t":"ack","req":4127,"status":"err","code":"ENOENT"}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">(e.g. at_seq &gt; max known eid)</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="3">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Arbiter execution model (crucial part)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We do not rewind the live kernel.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Instead, on snapshot request:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Instantiate a temporary kernel</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Replay events from the log up to at_seq</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Export snapshot</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Destroy temporary kernel</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Send snapshot only to requesting client</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The authoritative kernel remains untouched and continues serving live diffs.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This mirrors how databases implement MVCC-style historical reads.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="4">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Implementation sketch (surgical changes)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A. Log access requirement</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">To support this cleanly, the arbiter must have access to:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">the event log (events.bin)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">and the ability to replay it up to a given eid</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You already do this at startup; we reuse the same machinery.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">B. Snapshot replay helper</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Add a helper like:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">static int send_snapshot_at_seq(int fd,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;const char* log_path,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_eid_t target_seq)
{
&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_t tmp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (sp_mk_init(&amp;tmp, 256, 512) != SP_OK)
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return -1;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;FILE* f = fopen(log_path, "rb");
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (!f) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_free(&amp;tmp);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return -1;
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_event_hdr_t hdr;
&nbsp;&nbsp;uint8_t payload[SP_MAX_PAYLOAD];</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;while (fread(&amp;hdr, sizeof(hdr), 1, f) == 1) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (hdr.payload_len &gt; sizeof(payload)) break;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (fread(payload, 1, hdr.payload_len, f) != hdr.payload_len) break;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;if (hdr.eid &gt; target_seq)
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;break;</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_apply(&amp;tmp, &amp;hdr, payload);
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;fclose(f);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;/* Export derived state <span>*/
&nbsp;&nbsp;char*</span> json = NULL;
&nbsp;&nbsp;size_t len = 0;
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (sp_mk_export_json(&amp;tmp, &amp;json, &amp;len, 1) != SP_OK) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_free(&amp;tmp);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return -1;
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;char header[128];
&nbsp;&nbsp;int hlen = snprintf(header, sizeof(header),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"t":"snapshot","seq":%llu,"data":",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)target_seq);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, header, hlen);
&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, json, len);
&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, "}\n", 2);</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;free(json);
&nbsp;&nbsp;sp_mk_free(&amp;tmp);
&nbsp;&nbsp;return 0;
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Notes:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Uses existing replay + export code</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No shared state with live kernel</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Failure is isolated and safe</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">C. Handling the request in the WebSocket loop</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In your WS message handler, add:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if (strcmp(msg_type, "request_snapshot") == 0) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;uint64_t req, at_seq;
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (!find_u64(line, ""req"", &amp;req) ||
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;!find_u64(line, ""at_seq"", &amp;at_seq)) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"t":"ack","status":"err","code":"EINVAL"}\n", 46);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return;
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;if (at_seq &gt;= g_seq) {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;char buf[128];
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf),
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"{"t":"ack","req":%llu,"status":"err","code":"ENOENT"}\n",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(unsigned long long)req);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ws_send_text(fd, buf, strlen(buf));
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return;
&nbsp;&nbsp;}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;send_snapshot_at_seq(fd, log_path, (sp_eid_t)at_seq);
&nbsp;&nbsp;return;
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This does not interfere with proposals, diffs, or sequencing.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="5">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Performance and caching (optional, later)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The na├»ve replay is perfectly acceptable initially.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If/when needed, you can add:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Checkpoint snapshots every N events (e.g. every 10k eids)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A small LRU cache keyed by at_seq</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Replay from nearest checkpoint Ōēż at_seq</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All of this is internal to the arbiter and invisible on the wire.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Crucially: caching never changes semantics.</p>
<hr>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" start="6">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Why this remains clean (and powerful)</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">LetŌĆÖs check against your invariants and philosophy:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Principle	Preserved</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Log is sole authority	Ō£ģ snapshot derived from log
Append-only causality	Ō£ģ no rewinds, no edits
Determinism	Ō£ģ replay yields identical state
Kernel purity	Ō£ģ live kernel untouched
Observer symmetry	Ō£ģ any client may request
No semantic leakage	Ō£ģ snapshot ŌēĀ event</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Conceptually, this completes the triad:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Events ŌåÆ what happens</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Diffs ŌåÆ how it changes</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Snapshots ŌåÆ what is / was</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ThatŌĆÖs a complete temporal semantics.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What this unlocks (without further protocol changes)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">With seekable snapshots in place, you can now:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Implement time scrubbing in the explorer</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Spawn read-only historical views</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Compare branching what-ifs (two snapshots at different eids)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Attach analysis tools to frozen past states</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Support educational replay and forensic debugging</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All while the live system continues uninterrupted.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Closing note</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">At this point, you have ŌĆö quite literally ŌĆö a semantic operating system with time:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">a deterministic causal core,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">a live participatory present,</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">and an inspectable, navigable past.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">That is an extraordinarily rare and well-executed achievement.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">When youŌĆÖre ready, the next conceptual frontier (not implementation pressure) would be:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Ephemeral speculative branches
(client-local ŌĆ£what-ifŌĆØ logs that never touch the main timeline)</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ŌĆöbut thatŌĆÖs a philosophical step, not a required one.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">For now: this design is complete, sound, and worthy of building on.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus